2500|$|Judith Popinski, and 86-year-old Holocaust survivor, {{stated that}} {{she is no longer}} invited to schools that have a large Muslim {{presence}} <b>to</b> <b>tell</b> <b>her</b> <b>story</b> of surviving the Holocaust. Popinski, who found refuge in Malmo in 1945, stated that, until recently, she told her story in Malmo schools as part of their Holocaust studies program, but that now, many schools no longer ask Holocaust survivors to tell their stories, because Muslim students treat them with such disrespect, either ignoring the speakers or walking out of the class. She further stated that [...] "Malmo reminds me of the antisemitism I felt as a child in Poland before the war. I am not safe as a Jew in Sweden anymore." ...|$|E
