2500|$|In the {{developing}} world, hip hop {{has made a}} considerable impact in the social context. Despite the lack of resources, hip hop has made considerable inroads. Due to limited funds, hip hop artists are forced to use very basic tools, and even graffiti, {{an important aspect of}} the hip hop culture, is constrained due to its unavailability to the average person. Hip hop has begun making inroads with more than black artists. There are number of other minority artists who are taking center stage as many first generation minority children come of age. One example is rapper Awkwafina, an Asian-American, who raps about being Asian as well as being female. She, like many others, use rap to express her experiences as a minority not necessarily to [...] "unite" [...] minorities together but <b>to</b> <b>tell</b> <b>her</b> <b>story.</b>|$|E
